.TH "batadv_bla_rx" 9 "batadv_bla_rx" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_bla_rx \- check packets coming from the mesh.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" batadv_bla_rx
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "unsigned short vid "  ","
.BI "int packet_type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "skb" 12
the frame to be checked
.IP "vid" 12
the VLAN ID of the frame
.IP "packet_type" 12
the batman packet type this frame came in
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
batadv_bla_rx avoidance checks if:
* we have to race for a claim
* if the frame is allowed on the LAN

In these cases, the skb is further handled by this function
.SH "RETURN"
true if handled, otherwise it returns false and the caller shall
further process the skb.
